        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Scholarship for Self Finance Colleges Students of NT/DNT&amp;quot; by the Social Justice and Empowerment Department, Government of Gujarat, aims to support students belonging to Nomadic Tribes and De-notified Tribes (NT/DNT) categories in accessing quality education in self-financed colleges by reducing the financial burden. Through this scheme, financial assistance of up to ₹50,000/- is provided to cover tuition fees, registration charges, education fees, and other scholarship-related expenses for students enrolled in self-financed colleges. The scheme is implemented by the Social Justice and Empowerment Department, Government of Gujarat, and seeks to empower NT/DNT students with improved access to higher education opportunities.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n- **Financial Assistance:** Up to ₹50,000/- for tuition fee, registration fee, education fee, and other scholarship-related charges.\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme \"Scholarship for Self Finance Colleges Students of NT/DNT\" by the Social Justice and Empowerment Department, Government of Gujarat, provides financial assistance to Nomadic and De-notified Tribe students for pursuing higher education in self-financed colleges.",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
